newsitem.title: AUSTRALIA: AWB Report-Stockfeed demand keeps wheat firm.
newsitem.headline: AWB Report-Stockfeed demand keeps wheat firm.

text.p: The Australian market for wheat, barley and triticale firmed this week following continued demand from Victorian dairies for feed stocks, the Australian Wheat Board (AWB) said in its weeekly grain market report.
Reasonable levels of grain were still held on farm, it said.
Some sales from New South Wales (NSW) were not enough to dampen the market, which may be waiting for the new financial year, it said.
NSW high protein milling wheat could soften as a result of held stocks and a lack of domestic milling demand, it said.
Over the week, the sorghum price fell to A$136.00 a tonne from A$143.00 cash to the Liverpool Plains area, while new crop canola fell to A$303.00 from A$309.00 a tonne delivered Port Melbourne.
